<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="802" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1930/27161:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-23T19:00:00-04:00">January
                                    23, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>193. For Tittmann. Your 11, January 12.<note n="18" xml:id="d802fn18">See
                                    <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> A reply along the lines
                            suggested by you meets with the Department’s approval should you be
                            questioned concerning the possible bombardment of Rome. For your
                            information this subject has had the active attention of the President
                            and ourselves. Mr. Taylor has discussed the matter with the Apostolic
                            Delegate who has undoubtedly communicated these conversations to the
                            Vatican.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>